310,http://www.armslist.com/posts/1807310,For Sale:  FOR SALE: COLT SINGLE ACTION ARMY (S.A.A) - TANAKA,"North Carolina, North Carolina, United States",$ 800,"Listed On: Tuesday, June 25, 2013",Handguns,Colt                                                                                ,no type,Single Action                                                                                ,Derringer,"The Tanaka SAAs are widely held as the most beautiful, accurately replicated and well made airsoft revolvers available. They are only sporadically made and are often totally unobtainable.
The box was fairly typical of Tanaka's other revolvers, except that the background to the photographic artwork on the lid was bright red, rather than the usual dark background.

The silver finish on this gun is nothing like the stainless finish on the S&W 629s, being a bright, highly polished chrome finish....The weight and balance of the gun is good and there is nothing visible on the gun that one could describe as a fault or blemish.

The hammer cocks to two positions, half cock to permit rotation of the cylinder for loading and full cock, for firing. Of course, being a Single Action revolver, the SAA needs manually cocking before each shot, like a springer. This is achieved simply by pulling back the hammer.

On the barrel's left side is the legend ""COLT SINGLE ACTION ARMY .45"", with ""COLT'S PTFA MFG. CO. HARTFORD CT. U.S.A."" on the top of the barrel. There are a couple of small proofing marks on the left side of the trigger guard.

There are Colt logos on the grips in the form of a rampant horse in an oval raised section and there's a small Colt horse logo next to the patent marks. If you turn the gun upside down, you will find the only Tanaka mark right on the front of the frame, where it reads ""ASGK""/""MFG.TANAKA"".
The foresight is tall and clear, but the rear sight is a simple groove in the top of the frame, making the sights rudimentary at best.

The overall finish is excellent. I could not find anything that looked like a brush mark or pitting and the consistency of the mirror finish chrome effect across the various parts and materials appears 100%, even under varying light conditions, which are often expose even very minor flaws.

o load extra BBs, over the standard six cylinder openings, you need to remove the magazine stored in the extractor rod, which is done by depressing the 'screw' at the front (on the underside) of it. You can then fill the magazine with BBs and replace the extractor rod.
The grips are black plastic, replicating hard rubber, The hammer certainly is metal, as is the trigger and cylinder.
As I have come to expect of Tanaka revolvers, the SAA seems to have all the main features of the real revolver accurately replicated, with the exception of removable shells.

The BBs can be pushed into open cylinder mouths and extra ones can be stored in the extractor rod (more on that later), whilst the gas is put into the cylinder (as on all other Tanaka revolvers I have seen) by opening the moving piece of the frame and using the, provided, gas can extension. You need to half cock the hammer to get the cylinder to rotate, as with the real thing and there is an evocative click each time the cylinder moves on a notch.

To load extra BBs, over the standard six cylinder openings, you need to remove the magazine stored in the extractor rod, which is done by depressing the 'screw' at the front (on the underside) of it. You can then fill the magazine with BBs and replace the extractor rod."

528,http://www.armslist.com/posts/1807528,"For Sale/Trade:  Smith & Wesson 500 w/ 4"" barrel","Plainfield, Illinois, United States","$ 1,100","Listed On: Tuesday, June 25, 2013",Handguns,Smith & Wesson                                                                                ,no type,Double / Single Action                                                                                ,Revolver,"Okay I'm open to a cash sale or trade on my S&W 500. I'm in no rush to move it so I'm going to wait for the right deal! Here are the answers to some common questions!
Are they any major scratches or imperfections?
Nope just normal wear on a firearm, looks brand new. It only has fired 70 rounds!
Is there a lot of re-coil?

Yes and no. If you go to the range with 300-350 grain loads, it feels less than a short barrel .44 magnum. The muzzle ""break"" on the end really keeps the nose from flipping. I would not recommend throwing 500grain lead balls in it unless you're really familiar with big caliber firearms.
How much is ammo?

Finding ammo can be tricky. You can generally find name brand ammo for $49.99 for a box of 20 (sounds expensive but you will not want to shoot it more than 20 times in 1 range visit I promise). If you are a less frugal shopper, mega sports always has it in stock for about $64.99 per box of 20.
Where can I shoot it?
I obviously have not asked everywhere, but you can shoot at at Article II and GAT guns any time, Mega Sports on weekdays only and never at Rinks. Any outdoor range should also let you shoot it."

923,http://www.armslist.com/posts/1807923,"For Sale:  Easy to get a New AR15 M4, Fast!","Bellevue, Factoria, Seattle, Washington","$ 1,100","Listed On: Tuesday, June 25, 2013",Rifles,American Tactical Imports                                                                                ,223/5.56 NATO                                                                                ,Semi-automatic                                                                                ,Rifle,"Your new AR15 is here waiting for you.

It does not have to be hard to buy a rifle. I enjoy being a gun owner and the AR15 is an awesome weapon system that more people should have access to. It's no wonder it is the most popular rifle in America.

When I bought my first AR through a dealer, it was a tedious and unnecessary process. I thought the background check was ""instant"", what a joke, the FBI said my application would require ""further review"", and that would take 5 more days. So, I had to leave the dealer without my rifle, which was already paid for! For 5 days I  waited and researched about the NICS system and wondered how much longer it would take for the process to finish. Finally the FFL sent me email to say that he could ""proceed"". Great, why couldn't this be done 5 days ago? And to add to that, I had to pay a transfer fee for the ""service"" provided! And who knows what they're going to do with form I had to fill out, with my Social Security number on it as well!

After this distinctively ""non-instant"" background check, I will do everything I can to avoid the hassle of going through dealers and the Government for by firearms purchases, and that’s why I am making it easy for you to get your new AR15 M4.
To buy this rifle:
1.You must be over 18 years old. If you look young, I will ask to look at your ID and confirm. I will NOT record your name or any personally identifiable information.
2.You must be legally allowed to own a rifle. I will ask you, ""Are you legally allowed to own a rifle, right here right now?"" you will say ""yes"". Your word is your bond.
No further questions, no paperwork. It really should not be a long stressful process!
Let's meet face to face locally in Factoria, and get you your new rifle!
pics of the rifle here: http://www.flickr.com/photos/97616003@N05/sets/REDACTED5399589/
Now, let's run through the features of your new AR15 M4:
The Barrel:
Chambered in 5.56 nato,
you can shoot both .223 caliber and  5.56 mm ammunition.
in a .223 barrel you cannot safely shoot 5.56 ammunition.
Nitride treated barrel,

shown by the ""N"" roll mark on the barrel itself. Nitride treating is an upgrade from the common chrome lining process. Nitride treatment makes the barrel last longer and increases accuracy by reducing the friction in the bore between the bullet and barrel.
16 inch length.
This is the most popular barrel length for AR's. It is a great balance between barrel length for close quarters maneuverability, and barrel length for accuracy.
1 x 9 Barrel twist
This allows a wide range of bullet weights to be used from 50 - 75 grain. This allows flexibility in the use of different .223 and 5.56 ammo, and flexibility in the range of those rounds.
With the right ammo you can reach out to 300 yards, with optics make that 500 yards
Barrel Material is Chrome Moly Steel.

This is a common steel alloy used for rifle barrels. The chromium allows the alloy to resist oxidation and corrosion, and the Molybdenum adds higher temperature resistance and overall strength to the barrel.
Flash Hider,

A2 design flash hider and muzzle rise compensator. The flash hider is threaded on the end of the barrel with a 1/2 x 28 thread. This allows you to customize the muzzle with an alternate compensator if you wish.
Front sight,

Iron sight with adjustable sight post. The front sight triangle is ""F"" marked. This is a desirable feature to make the sight usable with the flat top M4 receiver. F marked sights are taller than the standard sights on non-M4 AR15's. The F actually stands for ""Flat"".
Front sight also has bayonet Lug. This lug works with M6 and M9 bayonets.
Also comes with front sling mount
Hand guards,

Hand guards are heat resistant polymer with a metal heat shield mounted inside. The hand guard length is the standard 7 inch Carbine length. This is very desirable, it makes it very easy to install aftermarket hand guards like a picatinny quad rail.
Upper Receiver
Aluminum Upper Manufactured by Anchor Harvey
Anchor Harvey is a well known manufacturer which supplies uppers to major AR manufacturers such as Colt and Bushmaster
Upper is marked with M4 above the front gas port.
This shows the upper is built to M4 specifications
Upper has T Marked flat top
The marks are part of the upper forging, and painted white. This allows you to replicate accessory placement if you take things like an optic off and on.
M4 Feed Ramps

The feed ramps are a highly desirable feature in M4's. it consists of two cuts along the bottom of the receiver and the barrel extension. This helps unfired rounds to enter the chamber quickly and allow the bolt to close faster after each shot.
Forward Assist Button

The forward assist lets you push the bolt forward in emergency cases where it may be jammed and preventing the bolt face to fully seat in the breech. In emergency situations Forward assist can be used to load a round without a magazine, or broken charging handle, or faulty buffer spring.  The forward assist can also be used to silently load a round without having to release the bolt carrier group with the charging handle.
Ejection port dust cover
The dust cover helps to keep debris out of the breech, bolt carrier group, magazine well, and barrel.
All Metal Rear Pop up sight

Included with this rifle is the Rear sight mounted on the top rail.Sight has standard windage adjustments and two apertures. Small aperture is for normal daylight shooting, large aperture is for night time and low light
Just add ammo and a mag and you're ready to rock and roll.
Bolt Carrier group
Chrome lined carrier
The bolt and firing pin move and rotate inside the bolt carrier. The chrome lining allows the bolt to move more reliably and makes the part easier to clean.
Properly Staked Gas Key
The gas key screws hold the gas key to the top of the bolt carrier. The screws are staked with a punch so that the screws can't work themselves loose during use. This is a highly desirable feature.
Black insert on shell Extractor
The black spring dampener is a desirable feature which increases the reliability of the shell extractor
Fully Shrouded firing pin

the shroud around the bottom of the bolt carrier group protects the firing pin and hammer during the rearward motion which cocks the hammer. The shroud smoothly cocks the hammer, instead of the firing pin. This is a highly desirable feature.
Lower Receiver
ATI Polymer TechComposite Lower

The non-metal receiver is strong and light. With this receiver the rifle is 6 pounds. Polymer is also NBC resistant, Nuclear, Biological and Chemical exposure will have minimal effect compared to machined aluminum. This lower will not show unsightly oil marks or scratch and dent like aluminum.
Glock pioneered the use of polymer lowers and many other manufactures are producing polymer firearms such as Springfield, Colt, Bushmaster, H&K, ect
Trigger group

Standard all metal trigger group with full profile hammer. Full profile hammer is a desirable feature. The full profile hammer allows conversion to pistol caliber rounds without having to change the hammer.
Low shelf internal pocket

The lower is of the Low Shelf type. This is a very highly desireable feature that allows a full auto trigger group to be installed in the lower. Currently full auto is not allowed for law abiding citizens.
Standard A2 pistol grip
Rear stock
Commercial buffer tube
The commercial size buffer tube is compatible with a wide range of accessories such as adjustable stocks and cheek rests and storage compartments
Six position sliding stock with metal sling mount.
Sliding stock control screw also contains a set pin inside the large thumb nut.
Removable Sliding stock
Stock can be removed from buffer tube to allow lower to be converted to AR pistol use with only changing the upper receiver
As you can see, there are a lot of features packed into this AR15 M4.
Once you get it, you can load and start shooting right away. This rifle has never been shot, used, or abused by any previous owners. It is just waiting for you to use and customize as You see fit!
Thank you for your time and consideration in buying this rifle.
Thanks Again!"
